# shadcn/ui Standards

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI components.

## Setup Commands

### Initialize shadcn/ui (if not already set up)
```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

### Add specific components as needed
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add input
```

## Usage Guidelines

- **Always use shadcn/ui components** instead of custom UI elements
- Check if a component exists in shadcn/ui before creating custom components
- Install missing components using the `npx shadcn@latest add [component]` command
- Components are installed to `src/components/ui/` and can be imported directly

## Example

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Use shadcn/ui components
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card"

export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <Button>Click me</Button>
    </Card>
  )
}

// ❌ AVOID - Creating custom UI from scratch
export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="border rounded p-4">
      <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2">
        Click me
      </button>
    </div>
  )
}
```